    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Cut your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and dice finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fennel-sausage-and-chilli-ragu-and-mafaldine-with-dough-balls/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until they have started to soften</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fennel-sausage-and-chilli-ragu-and-mafaldine-with-dough-balls/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has started to soften, add your <strong>sausage meat</strong> (remove the paper if required!) with your <strong>fennel seeds</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until starting to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fennel-sausage-and-chilli-ragu-and-mafaldine-with-dough-balls/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the sausage is cooking, add your <strong>mafaldine</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the mafaldine for 7-9 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the mafaldine, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fennel-sausage-and-chilli-ragu-and-mafaldine-with-dough-balls/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Reboil half a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>dough balls </strong>to a baking tray (set the <strong>dip</strong> aside so it comes to room temperature)</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 5-7 min or until golden brown</p><p>Once the sausage is starting to colour, reduce the heat to medium and add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>diced chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fennel-sausage-and-chilli-ragu-and-mafaldine-with-dough-balls/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> with your <strong>clotted cream</strong>, 100ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [130ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [170ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 4-5 min or until the sauce has thickened and the sausage is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>fennel sausage & chilli rag\u00f9</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fennel-sausage-and-chilli-ragu-and-mafaldine-with-dough-balls/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the rag\u00f9 has thickened, add the <strong>cooked mafaldine</strong> with the <strong>reserved starchy pasta water</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>grated</strong> <strong>pecorino cheese</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) and a generous grind of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 30 secs further or until thickened and saucy \u2013 this is your <strong>fennel sausage & chilli rag\u00f9 with mafaldine</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fennel-sausage-and-chilli-ragu-and-mafaldine-with-dough-balls/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>fennel sausage & chilli rag\u00f9 with mafaldine </strong>and garnish with the <strong>remaining grated pecorino cheese</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>salad</strong> to the side and drizzle over your <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> with a little <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
